a0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">This document has been prepared by Bank of Ireland UK (BOIUK) in response to the Northern Ireland Affairs Committee Call for Evidence: The Banking Structure in No</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">rthern Ireland, 16</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> July 2013. BOIUK is committed to providing the fullest cooperation with the Committee during the conduct of this Inquiry. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Executive Summary</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Bank of Ireland has a long established business in Northern Ireland and continues to extend </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">significant support to our customers and the region and its economy through the products and services provided under both the BOIUK “brand” and through our partnership with UK Post Office</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOIUK recognises the significant changes to the banking market in th</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">e region since 2007/08 and the continuing challenges from the operating environment but is determined to play its part in supporting recovery. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">During 2012, the Board of BOI (UK) plc reaffirmed its commitment to Northern Ireland as a “core franchise” and u</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">nderlined its support with a very significant investment programme which is underway. Recent strategic changes to BOIUK in the region have the objective of restoring the bank to profitability, establishing a platform for future growth and generating an acc</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">eptable return for shareholders. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">the</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> context of a period of severe economic recession and reduced levels of economic activity</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> BOIUK recognises that the demand for credit remains constrained</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> BOIUK is supportive of initiatives such as expanding the reg</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ional dataset that might assist a better understanding of market trends and to help in policymaking.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.25pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.25pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2.0</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Background - Overview of Bank of Ireland (BOI)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2.1</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">B</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ank of Ireland Group (BOIG)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Established in 1783, BOI has been a key part of the Irish banking</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> system, across the island for 230 years and has been present in Great Britain for over 40 years, incorporating as a full subsidiary in the UK in November 2010. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOI is the largest Irish bank by total assets and capital value and with over 1 million custom</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ers and leading market positions, is a systemically important retail and commercial bank playing a critical role in the operation of the Irish economy.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOI has an international presence through its franchise businesses in the UK and its partnership with th</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">e Post Office with our 2.5m customers and niche lending activities in the US and Europe. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2.2</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Bank of Ireland in the UK </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOIUK Retail division is led by CEO Des Crowley and currently employs over 2,000 staff and leverages BOI Group for specialist and scale services. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOI continues to be a “net lender” to the UK economy, while deleveraging non-core lending portfolios. Total l</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">oans of c£33bn include over £21bn of mortgages with deposits of c£22bn from Northern Ireland, Business Banking GB and the Post Office.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOIUK plc, a 100% owned subsidiary of Bank of Ireland Group, was incorporated by the FSA on 1</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">st</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> November 2010, is authori</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">sed by the PRA and regulated by the PRA and FCA. This enables BOI to offer products and services in the UK market, including Northern Ireland, that are directly comparable to existing providers from a risk and protection standpoint. Funds placed with BOIUK</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> plc are protected by the UK’s Financial Services Compensation Scheme (FSCS) up to £85,000, the same as other UK banks and building societies.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOIUK plc manages its own balance sheet with separate capital, liquidity and funding requirements as per the UK r</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">egulatory framework. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOIUK plc has independent governance arrangements with a Board of Directors comprising a mix of executive, independent non-executives, including the chairman, and non-executive directors from BOI Group. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2.3</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The Partnership </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">with the UK Post Office (PO)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOIUK plc has exclusive distribution rights for consumer financial services throughout the PO’s unrivalled 11,500 strong branch network, including Northern Ireland. The partnership with the PO commenced in 2004 and during 2012</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> the contract was extended </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">to a </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">minimum of 2023</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">As of 2013, this relationship includes 2.75 million financial services customers across a range of products including mortgages, deposits, insurance customers, unsecured consumer loans, FRES, and credit car</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ds. In addition, there is a network of 2200 ATMs while PO also serves 1 in 4 over the counter foreign exchange customers in the UK. More recently, BOIUK plc launched a pilot of three new </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">PO branded </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">personal current accounts via the PO network.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">PO products </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">are distributed via the PO branch network as well via direct channels - online and telephone.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">UK PO in NI</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">There are a total of c. 75 PO branches in NI</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Based on June 2013 data, there were c. 20,000 PO credit card holders based in NI; c. 35,500 savings ac</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">counts;</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">c. 25,500 insurance customers (across motor, home and life insurance products) and </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">c. 200 PO mortgage customers (</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">a new product line).</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2.4</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Bank of Ireland in Northern Ireland (BOI NI)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOI NI operates a full service retail and business bank </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">in the region providing products and services to c 200,000 customers, distributed via a network of 35 branches, a workforce of 12,850 including c. 130 specialist business bankers, complemented by a direct banking proposition of telephone and online channel</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">s and Post Office financial services.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOI NI’s share of the consumer market in the region ranges from c 5% in mortgages to 10% in personal current accounts</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> with a share in the business market of 15-20%, across segments of small, medium and larger companie</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">s. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Nick Fahy is MD Northern Ireland &amp; Distribution Director UK. The other roles in the management team include Regional Manager (Head of Network); Head of Business Banking; and Head of Development &amp; Marketing. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In addition to the franchise business in Nor</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">thern Ireland, BOIUK also has responsibility for the Northern Ireland Note issue, by Act of Parliament, and operates the car and asset finance business, NIIB, which also trades in Great Britain under the Northridge Finance brand. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.25pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.25pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">3.0</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Overview of the</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Banking</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> market in Northern Ireland </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">For a population of 1.8 million and c 70,000 VAT and PAYE-only registered businesses, the banking market in Northern Ireland is a very competitive one with a large number of suppliers of financial services operating in the mar</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ket with a range of multi-channel and direct propositions. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOI NI competes in both consumer and business segments against the other NI Clearing banks, a number of large international and national banks and brands, UK and local building societies and a num</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ber of niche and direct-only providers. In addition, both the PO and Credit Union movement have a larger presence in the local market, relative to the rest of the UK, as providers of financial services. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The competitive nature of the Northern Ireland</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> banking market has been reflected in a number of ways, including the compression of credit margins on business loans, price intensity on deposits and fragmented market shares across a number of products.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOIUK believes that competition is in the interes</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ts of consumers, the Bank and its shareholders. A competitive economy requires a competitive banking sector and, over many years, BOIUK has responded through increased</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">customer-focus and by being more innovative in the range of products and services we pr</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ovide and the channels through which they are transmitted. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The global financial crisis of 2007-08, severe local recession and unwinding of a pronounced residential property boom ha</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ve</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> pushed the regional banking market into a loss position, with elevated l</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">evels of impairments and a very difficult operating environment. The market is now in a period of slow recovery with conditions improving as economic confidence and business activity levels rise and, in time, interest rates begin to normalise. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The landsca</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">pe for retail banking for all regions of the UK has changed significantly in the period since 2007-08 and is likely to change further in the coming years. BOI NI is adapting to the change and sees opportunities to further develop its business in the region</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4.0</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">BOIUK Strategic Priorities for the business in Northern Ireland</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">During 2012, the Board of BOIUK reaffirmed Northern Ireland as a “core franchise” and identified a number of key strategic objectives for the business with a clear plan and str</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ong focus on restoring profitability and ensuring a sustainable business model for the longer term. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The strategy for growth has a number of key objectives aimed at establishing BOI NI as a Top 3 business bank, with strong and profitable growth in key cons</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">umer segments including mortgages and current accounts. This is based on a number of pillars including: </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 90pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:8pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">An intense focus on our customers and building long-term relationships that will help support the recovery of the Northern Ireland economy</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 90pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:8pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">provision of new lending to both consumers and businesses</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 90pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:8pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">A significant investment in the franchise’s distribution channels, quality of service and range of products. </span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The strategic objectives and initiatives for the business in Northern Ireland are fully </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">aligned with both BOIG and BOIUK objectives. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">5.0</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Banking with Bank of Ireland in Northern Ireland </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOIUK is a “multi-channel” provider of financial services in Northern Ireland both in our own “brand” and through the partnership with the PO. Our </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">customers transact business on their accounts, seek financial advice and purchase financial products via a number of both traditional and direct channels including:</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 90pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:8pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">An extensive network of 35 branches with a geographical spread across the region, complemen</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ted by almost 200 onsite and retailer ATMS and an additional 28 with the PO.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 90pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:8pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">A comprehensive suite of telephone, mobile and online banking services</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 90pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:8pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">A range of banking services provided to BOIUK customers via the PO. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">These include:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 90pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:8pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Balance enquiries using</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> a BOIUK card and PIN</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 90pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:8pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Cash deposit with a BOIUK card or lodgement slip and same day value</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 90pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:8pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Cash withdrawals with a BOIUK card </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 90pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Wingdings; font-size:8pt"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa