ting to a total investment of c£10 million, this represents a material commitment by BOIUK to the NI market and will be a very positive development for all who use t</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">hese branches, giving easy access to banking services in an environment that better reflects the changing needs of customers. BOIUK also opened a new location, Belfast City Hall, in the new branch model format, during 2012. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In addition to the investment, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOIUK also announced the closure of 9 of our smaller branch locations, including the merger of 2 small outlets in the City of Derry/Londonderry into our commercial branch on Strand Road. In aggregate, the branches that have subsequently closed accounted fo</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">r a relatively small percentage of the business conducted by the network in NI. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The decisions taken by BOIUK with regard to specific locations were the result of a detailed and robust assessment of a broad range of criteria including financial performance</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> and profitability over a long period of time, market and demographic trends, potential future requirements and the proximity to other BOIUK branches. Changes in customer behaviour and growing use of new technologies and the impact on levels of branch usag</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">e also led us to conclude that the volume and type of business generated in these smaller locations was insufficient to sustain them on a profitable basis. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The decision to close a branch is not taken lightly nor without due consideration to the potential </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">impact on our customers and staff and the range of options or alternatives available to continue banking with BOIUK. In particular, BOIUK has highlighted the importance of the local PO for customers who may wish to transact business in a location no longer</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> served by a branch</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Changes to the network were accompanied </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">by</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> an extensive programme of communication with impacted customers and stakeholders. We are pleased to report high levels of customer retention. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOIUK has no current plans to </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">further </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">reduce its</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> network in Northern Ireland. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">7.0</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Access to Finance in Northern Ireland </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.61pt; padding-left:8.09pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">As a net lender to the NI marketplace, BOIUK continues to provide significant support to customers in the region but is clear that the full recovery of the bank requires the </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">origination of new and existing customer loans on the balance sheet, particularly to the SME/Business segment.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.61pt; padding-left:8.09pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOIUK is therefore keen to stress that we are open for business, with capacity to lend to viable propositions and are actively seeking new lendin</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">g opportunities across all sectors. This message was reinforced earlier this year in a high profile TV and media campaign. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">While</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> the economy is showing signs of stabilisation and sentiment is improving, demand conditions remain relatively subdued, as conf</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">irmed by independent research reports during 2013</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">. Redemptions; the paying down of debt and the accumulation of cash reserves; remain at relatively high levels for some businesses while for others, uncertainty about the economic climate has led to </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">deferred investment decisions. Some firms are encumbered with property-related debts with other banks.</span></li></ul><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.91pt; padding-left:7.79pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOIUK is approving c 90% of applications for credit but with a significant challenge in moving some customers from “approval” to “drawdown”. We have esta</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">blished a new Business Acquisition Team to focus on developing a stronger pipeline of new opportunities. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.91pt; padding-left:7.79pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOIUK has introduced a number of specific initiatives in recent times to support business customers and stimulate a greater demand for credit, includi</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ng a £100 million agri-fund, an export finance initiative and a partnership with Invest NI and the Northern Ireland Science Park to support growth businesses in high technology, R&amp;D and export-focused sectors. Broader support for the NI SME/business sector</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> includes “BOIUK Enterprise Weeks” of events, and seminars with opportunities for SMEs to showcase their businesses in BOIUK branches. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.91pt; padding-left:7.79pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOIUK is also fully supportive of Invest NI’s Access to Finance</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">schemes and the implementation of the BBA Better Busines</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">s Finance Initiatives including the New Lending Code, Mentoring and Appeals Process. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.91pt; padding-left:7.79pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">For NI consumers, BOI has introduced a £200 million mortgage fund, currently running to the end of 2013, and has demonstrated strong support to Northern Ireland Co-Owners</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">hip Housing Association (NICHA) with direct funding and the development of a specific mortgage product. </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">8.0</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">UK National credit initiatives</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.61pt; padding-left:8.09pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOIUK welcomes any government initiative that can help stimulate the flow of credit to viable businesses and aids</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> economic recovery in Northern Ireland. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.61pt; padding-left:8.09pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOIUK has been a participant in the Enterprise Finance Guarantee Scheme although demand has been limited and drawdowns modest under the scheme. In most cases, BOIUK has been able to provide the finance to the borrow</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">er via more cost effective products such as our Essentials for Business package. BOIUK plans to launch a new Small Business &amp; Agriculture proposition later in 2013 aimed at start-up and growth companies. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.61pt; padding-left:8.09pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOIUK became a member of the Bank of England’s Ster</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ling Monetary Framework in February 2013, a prerequisite to participation in Funding for Lending Scheme (FLS). BOIUK made an initial £250m drawdown under FLS in June and will consider further phased usage later in 2013 and into 2014, linked </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">to the prevaili</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ng cost of funds in retail deposit market and consistent with BOI Group’s agreed plan with the EU.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.61pt; padding-left:8.09pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOIUK understands that the current UK Help-to-Buy scheme may have only limited application to Northern Ireland market. However, BOIUK will continue to sup</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">port the region’s “shared equity” model through its relationship with NICHA. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.61pt; padding-left:8.09pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Irrespective of government schemes, BOIUK has the capital, liquidity and infrastructure to serve its growth ambitions in the regional marketplace. The biggest challenge remains t</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">he subdued demand for finance in the context of current lower levels of economic activity. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">9.0</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Regional lending data </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:120%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.61pt; padding-left:8.09pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOIUK is strongly supportive of expanding the regional dataset to include other institutions for a more complete picture of the market and also to see if more granular information can be provided on a common platform. BOIUK has suggested that the quarterly</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> mandatory returns to the BoE provided by all the banks might be the best vehicle to expedite this.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.61pt; padding-left:8.09pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOIUK has also supported the recent all-island study by Mazars and will </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">engage positively with BBA and other stakeholders on any proposals for extending </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">UK postcode lending and deposits datasets to the region. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">10.0</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Summary </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOIUK is ambitious for the growth of its business in NI and in supporting the recovery of the regional economy. We believe our plans and actions, including significant investment, repre</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">sent a clear signal of our intent to grow our business despite what remains a challenging operating environment. It is critical we have profitable activities in order to secure a strong, viable business in the region that will support customers and protect</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> jobs in the long-term. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BOIUK hopes the content of this document is helpful in providing insights into the market in Northern Ireland and assists the committee’s understanding of the operation of the bank in the region. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">August 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:right"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">Page </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">1</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">6</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">“Access to Finance”, Economic Advisory Group, March 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-indent:7.1pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> SME Finance Monitor, Q1 2013, BDRC May 2013</span></p></body></html>